{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Under the mistletoe
[D7]The girls all stood [G7]around
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
But the one dressed in a cloud of blue
[C]Was the pretties girl in town
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Under the mistletoe
[D7]She waited [G7]patiently
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
So I walked across the room
[C]And held her close to me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[G7]Her eyes were so inviting
[C]And her lips were so divine
[G7]When she smiled I kissed her
[F]And I knew that she was [G7]mine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[C]Now we still talk about
[F]That Christmas [G7]day so long [C]ago
[D7]When we kissed and fell in [G7]love
[C]Under the mistletoe
{end_of_verse}

